Program: The Documentary
Title: All That Stands in the Way - The Parents
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01z1r84
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 24 May 2014
The parents of four teenage girls in the BBC World Service programme All That Stands In The Way, meet and talk for the first time. What did they think of the freedoms and limits to each girl’s life and has the documentary made them reconsider their views on trust, discipline, relationships and fashion. As their children reach adulthood and independence what do they think of gender equality and their daughter’s chance in the modern world? Show less